<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd" []>
<task xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" id="specifying-autosave-settings" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:oasis:names:tc:dita:xsd:task.xsd:1.1">
  <title>Specifying Autosave Settings</title>
  <taskbody id="body">
    <context>
      <p>When you work with a document, Serna can save it automatically at a predetermined interval to avoid data loss in case of a crash or freeze.</p>
      <p>To specify  autosave settings, do the follwoing:</p>
    </context>
    <steps>
      <step>
        <cmd>Call up the <keyword>Preferences Dialog</keyword>.</cmd>
        <info>
          <p>To call up the <keyword>Preferences Dialog</keyword>, choose <menucascade>
              <uicontrol>Tools</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>Preferences</uicontrol>
            </menucascade>.</p>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Select the <keyword>General tab</keyword>.</cmd>
        <info>
          <fig>
            <title>General tab.</title>
            <image href="preferences-dialog-general-tab-autosave.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
          </fig>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Enable autosave.</cmd>
        <info>
          <p>To enable document auto-saving, check the <uicontrol>Autosave every ... minutes</uicontrol> checkbox on the <uicontrol>Autosave</uicontrol> pane.</p>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>In the spinner, specify the interval at which a document should be auto-saved.</cmd>
        <info>
          <p>The default value is 10 minutes.</p>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Apply</uicontrol> button to apply the settings.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Close</uicontrol> button to close the dialog.</cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
</task>
